  "prompt": "Where can I get a red coat, like Joaquin Phoenix used to wear in the movie Her, in India?",
  "response": "Finding a red coat similar to the one Joaquin Phoenix wore in \"Her\" can involve a few steps. Here are some suggestions to help you find one in India:\n\n1. **Online Shopping Websites**: Popular e-commerce platforms such as Amazon India, Flipkart, Myntra, and Ajio often have a wide range of clothing options. You can search for a \"red coat\" or \"red jacket\" on these sites and filter by style, brand, and price. For more specific cinematic styles, you might want to try international platforms that ship to India like ASOS or Farfetch.\n\n2. **Boutique Stores**: Visit specialized fashion stores or boutiques in major cities like Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, or Kolkata. Stores that offer designer wear or vintage styles may have unique pieces.\n\n3. **Custom Tailoring**: For a more precise match to the coat from \"Her,\" consider getting one tailored. Many cities have skilled tailors and bespoke clothing stores where you can show a picture of the coat and get a custom-made version.\n\n4. **Thrift and Vintage Stores**: Check out thrift shops or vintage clothing stores. They often carry unique items and might have something similar. Look for known thrift stores in cities or online platforms that deal in vintage clothing.\n\n5. **Fashion Events and Expos**: Attend local fashion events or expos that feature a variety of designers and brands. You might find something similar to Joaquin Phoenix's coat here.\n\n6. **Social Media and Forums**: Platforms like Instagram, Pinterest, and Reddit have communities and influencers who share fashion tips and online store recommendations. Search for hashtags like #RedCoat or #HerMovieFashion or participate in relevant forums.\n\nRemember to check customer reviews and return policies when ordering online to ensure quality and fit. Happy shopping!",
